The '''Essence Stealer''' was a device invented by [[Borborygmus Gog]] as part of [[Project Starscream]]. It was designed to rip the [[The Force/Legends|Force]]-essence out of a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi's]] body and contain it. Its victims' bodies were stored in stasis pods while their essence was collectively held in a crystal globe. Gog used the technology from a [[Ssi-ruu|Ssi-Ruuvi]] [[Swarm-class battle droid]] that he had purchased from [[Raith Sienar/Legends|Raith Sienar]]. He placed it in the Jedi library on the [[Nespis VIII]] [[Space station/Legends|space station]]. This experiment was based on a theory by [[Jenna Zan Arbor]]. The [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] [[Human/Legends|Human]], [[Tash Arranda/Legends|Tash Arranda]], managed to destroy it with the help of her uncle, [[Mammon Hoole]].

The insane [[Scientist/Legends|scientist]], [[Umak Leth]] used similar technology in developing the [[Universal Energy Cage]].

